cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with aligning 3D CAD models to RGB-D scans, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as feature detection and matching. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves robotics (RO) as it deals with aligning CAD models to real-world scans, and machine learning (LG) as it uses a CNN architecture to learn a joint embedding between real and synthetic objects. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (AI) as it uses a data-driven approach to align CAD models to scans.
